WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Hannah and the Hurricane by John Escott. Penguin readers, easy start.

00:23.000 --> 00:29.000
Hannah is 16 and lives on an island. She is on holiday from school

00:29.000 --> 00:34.000
and is working for Mr. Duval on his glass-bottomed boat.

00:34.000 --> 00:39.000
They take people to look at the beautiful fish and the coral reef under the sea.

00:39.000 --> 00:47.000
Mr. Duval can only pay Hannah a little money, but she likes working for the old man.

00:47.000 --> 00:53.000
Mr. Duval's boat is the only glass-bottomed boat on the island.

00:53.000 --> 00:57.000
But one day...

00:57.000 --> 01:03.000
Look Mr. Duval, says Hannah. There's a new glass-bottomed boat.

01:03.000 --> 01:09.000
Hannah is right. The new boat is taking people out to look at the coral reef

01:09.000 --> 01:13.000
and there are people waiting for it to come back.

01:13.000 --> 01:18.000
Why are all the people going on the new boat and not on my boat?

01:18.000 --> 01:20.000
Says Mr. Duval.

01:20.000 --> 01:22.000
What's happening?

01:22.000 --> 01:26.000
I'm going to find out, says Hannah.

01:33.000 --> 01:38.000
Hannah soon has the answer. It's cheaper, she says.

01:38.000 --> 01:42.000
Yes, says a man standing behind her.

01:42.000 --> 01:49.000
And it's going to be the only glass-bottomed boat on the island in a month or two.

01:49.000 --> 01:54.000
It's going to be goodbye, Mr. Duval.

01:54.000 --> 02:01.000
And he laughs. Hannah knows the man. His name is Max Marker.

02:01.000 --> 02:06.000
He is very rich and has a big house on the island.

02:06.000 --> 02:08.000
Is it your boat?

02:08.000 --> 02:09.000
She asks.

02:09.000 --> 02:13.000
Yes, he says.

02:13.000 --> 02:17.000
Why is it cheaper on your boat? Hannah asks.

02:17.000 --> 02:20.000
Oh, I know, she says.

02:20.000 --> 02:27.000
You want to stop Mr. Duval's boat and then your prices can go up.

02:27.000 --> 02:29.000
Max smiles.

02:29.000 --> 02:35.000
Come and work for me, he says. I can pay you lots of money.

02:35.000 --> 02:38.000
No, says Hannah.

02:38.000 --> 02:43.000
I like working for Mr. Duval. Money isn't everything.

02:43.000 --> 02:57.000
You're wrong, says Max. He's laughing again, but it is not a nice laugh.

02:57.000 --> 03:03.000
The weeks go by. People do not come to Mr. Duval's boat.

03:03.000 --> 03:12.000
I'm sorry, but there is no more work for you, Hannah, says Mr. Duval one day.

03:12.000 --> 03:19.000
It's okay, says Hannah, but she is very sad to lose her job.

03:19.000 --> 03:22.000
Max goes to see the old man.

03:22.000 --> 03:27.000
Do you want to sell your boat? He asks.

03:27.000 --> 03:30.000
I can give you a good price for it.

03:30.000 --> 03:33.000
Mr. Duval is very angry.

03:33.000 --> 03:36.000
No, he says.

03:36.000 --> 03:43.000
The next morning Mr. Duval goes to his boat and sees that it is under the water.

03:43.000 --> 03:49.000
Oh, no, he says. I don't understand.

03:49.000 --> 03:52.000
Hannah comes later that morning.

03:52.000 --> 03:58.000
The radio says there is a strong storm coming, a hurricane.

03:58.000 --> 04:03.000
She wants to help Mr. Duval get his boat into the boat house,

04:03.000 --> 04:09.000
but now she sees the glass bottomed boat under the water.

04:09.000 --> 04:16.000
This is Max Marker's work, says Hannah. He wants to destroy your business.

04:16.000 --> 04:20.000
I'm an old man, says Mr. Duval.

04:20.000 --> 04:26.000
I'm too tired to fight Max Marker and his nasty games.

04:26.000 --> 04:32.000
I'm not, says Hannah. I'm going to his house to see him.

04:32.000 --> 04:36.000
But it is too late. The hurricane is coming.

04:36.000 --> 04:44.000
We must get to my house, says Mr. Duval.

04:44.000 --> 04:48.000
The hurricane hits the island at 11 o'clock that morning.

04:48.000 --> 04:54.000
It pulls trees from the ground and they crash down on houses.

04:54.000 --> 04:59.000
Cars roll across the road like children's toys.

04:59.000 --> 05:04.000
Soon, many of the island's roads are under water.

05:04.000 --> 05:11.000
The strong wind throws Max Marker's boat out of the water and against a wall.

05:11.000 --> 05:20.000
Hannah and Mr. Duval are safe in a room under the old man's house.

05:20.000 --> 05:24.000
The hurricane goes on for four hours.

05:24.000 --> 05:29.000
Slowly, the wind gets weaker and weaker.

05:29.000 --> 05:34.000
Two hours later, people start to come out of their houses.

05:34.000 --> 05:39.000
The rain stops.

05:39.000 --> 05:45.000
Now I can go to see Max Marker about his nasty games, says Hannah.

05:45.000 --> 05:49.000
What can you do, says Mr. Duval?

05:49.000 --> 05:51.000
How can you stop him?

05:51.000 --> 05:55.000
I don't know, says Hannah angrily.

05:55.000 --> 06:00.000
But I can do something and she runs off.

06:06.000 --> 06:10.000
Hannah goes to Max Marker's big house.

06:10.000 --> 06:13.000
She sees the work of the hurricane.

06:13.000 --> 06:16.000
Some of his house is gone.

06:16.000 --> 06:19.000
Where is Max Marker?

06:19.000 --> 06:23.000
She thinks. Is he inside?

06:23.000 --> 06:27.000
She starts to run to the house, but she is afraid.

06:27.000 --> 06:34.000
Max Marker is inside the house and he cannot get out.

06:34.000 --> 06:37.000
Help! Help!

06:37.000 --> 06:42.000
He says, I'm going to die!

06:42.000 --> 06:46.000
The wind takes his words and carries them away.

06:46.000 --> 06:52.000
Hannah can hear Max Marker, but she cannot see him.

06:52.000 --> 06:54.000
Where are you?

06:54.000 --> 07:00.000
She says, here! He says, I'm over here!

07:00.000 --> 07:03.000
Suddenly, she sees him.

07:03.000 --> 07:07.000
He's not laughing now, she thinks.

07:07.000 --> 07:12.000
There are stones and some of the roof on top of him.

07:12.000 --> 07:15.000
Help me! He cries.

07:15.000 --> 07:18.000
Please! I'm coming!

07:18.000 --> 07:27.000
She tells him, Hannah climbs across and starts to pull the stones off him.

07:30.000 --> 07:36.000
It is not easy. The stones are very heavy.

07:36.000 --> 07:41.000
She gets one off him.

07:41.000 --> 07:46.000
Then the next one.

07:46.000 --> 07:51.000
Faster! He tells her, work faster!

07:51.000 --> 07:55.000
I can't! She cries.

07:55.000 --> 07:59.000
Suddenly, there is a noise above her.

07:59.000 --> 08:04.000
Hannah looks up. Some of the roof is coming down.

08:04.000 --> 08:06.000
Help!

08:06.000 --> 08:12.000
Says Max, and he starts to cry.

08:12.000 --> 08:25.000
Hannah jumps away and the roof crashes down near her.

08:25.000 --> 08:30.000
She waits for ten seconds and she can see again.

08:30.000 --> 08:34.000
She climbs back across the stones to Max Marker.

08:34.000 --> 08:38.000
He is very happy to see her.

08:38.000 --> 08:42.000
How long before all the house comes down?

08:42.000 --> 08:46.000
Things, Hannah. Can I get him out quickly?

08:46.000 --> 08:51.000
She starts to work faster.

08:51.000 --> 08:56.000
Max can move now, but he is very weak.

08:56.000 --> 09:00.000
He stands up slowly. Then he climbs out of the house.

09:00.000 --> 09:05.000
Hannah helps him across the street. They look back.

09:05.000 --> 09:08.000
The house crashes to the ground.

09:14.000 --> 09:18.000
But Max Marker is smiling now.

09:18.000 --> 09:20.000
You're very brave.

09:20.000 --> 09:24.000
He says, thank you, my friend.

09:24.000 --> 09:29.000
I'm not your friend, says Hannah.

09:29.000 --> 09:32.000
How can I pay you?

09:32.000 --> 09:33.000
Says Max.

09:33.000 --> 09:40.000
Pay for Mr. Duval's boat, says Hannah, and stop your nasty games.

09:40.000 --> 09:45.000
Work together with the two boats. Don't fight.

09:45.000 --> 09:49.000
Okay, says Max Marker.

09:49.000 --> 09:52.000
But what can I give you?

09:52.000 --> 09:56.000
I don't want anything, says Hannah.

09:56.000 --> 10:00.000
Some money, asks Max.

10:00.000 --> 10:03.000
No thank you, says Hannah.

10:03.000 --> 10:06.000
Money isn't everything.

10:06.000 --> 10:08.000
Yes.

10:08.000 --> 10:13.000
I'm starting to understand that, says Max.

10:22.000 --> 10:25.000
Thank you.

10:52.000 --> 10:55.000
Thank you.

